003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Preston of Craigmiller was born in 1300, in Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1300–":"1300–Surnud","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1300–":"1300–Kuollut","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1300–":"1300–Décédé","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Preston of Craigmiller est né en 1300, à Craigmillar, Midlothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1300–":"1300–Verstorben","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–Verstorben","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Preston of Craigmiller wurde 1300 in Craigmillar, Midlothian, Schottland, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1300–":"1300–Desede","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–Desede","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Ecosse, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1300–":"1300–elhunyt","1325–1345":"1325–1345","1300–Male":"1300–el